Copy their files onto the server (usually fullchain.pem and privkey.pem). A common location is /etc/ssl/homestay/. Example:

sudo mkdir -p /etc/ssl/homestay
sudo cp fullchain.pem /etc/ssl/homestay/homestay.crt
sudo cp privkey.pem /etc/ssl/homestay/homestay.key
sudo chmod 640 /etc/ssl/homestay/*
sudo chown root:root /etc/ssl/homestay/*

Edit the nginx site /etc/nginx/sites-available/homestay-r1.conf:

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name customer-domain.com;
    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
}

server {
    listen 443 ssl http2;
    server_name customer-domain.com;

    ssl_certificate     /etc/ssl/homestay/homestay.crt;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/ssl/homestay/homestay.key;

    # ...existing proxy blocks (same as your HTTP config)...

}
Test and reload nginx:

sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx